summary:
What would I do in paradise,
When you're sleeping next to me?
Let others have their paradise,
I don't want it. 
- Orelsan
I love...
body:
What would I do in paradise,

When you’re sleeping next to me?

Let others have their paradise,

I don’t want it.

- Orelsan

I love these lyrics because I feel like they apply to Tony so well. He’s going to heaven but what would he do there? He already had his paradise. His paradise is what he leaves behind. A wife and daughter.

So no, his death wasn’t a beautiful ending.

Additional Tags: Avengers: Endgame (Movie) Spoilers, Fix-It, Yes that means reversing that one death, ft. a supernatural being, no beta we die like men, also i tagged major character death but he does come back, Resurrection
Summary:

Warning: Contains Avengers: Endgame Spoilers. Read at your own risk

“You can rest now.”

 Yes. Yes, that’s what he wanted. The world was saved but everything hurt and he just wanted to close his eyes. With Pepper’s permission, he finally got his rest. Some screamed, others cried, but Tony couldn’t hear them anymore.

He took his last breath, felt his last heart beat, and closed his eyes.

 And then he opened his eyes.

summary: Shadowed Hearts and Winter Souls (WinterIron)(Masterlist)
title: Shadowed Hearts and Winter Souls (WinterIron)(Masterlist)
body:
(Author’s Note: This is my Ko-Fi Supporter Exclusive fic, chapters are posted weekly on my KO-FI PAGE, posted once a month here and on AO3) 

**********************

The mid-1800s and Antonio Carbonell Stark is caught in a scandal with his lover. Desperate for a chance to escape the trouble and his own broken heart, Tony accepts a proposal from a mysterious Russian heiress and flees the country.

Natalia Romanova is in trouble of her own and has enough secrets to make Tony’s head spin but somehow they settle into a fake marriage and calm day-to-day together, and everything works… until her half brother comes home and their life is disrupted again.

Bucky is somber and silent, brutal and nearly broken and scarred, a soldier of the resistance. His
heart is cold and gaze like ice, but his hands are hot and lips are warm and Tony finds himself ignoring the blood on Bucky’s palms and the shadows in his soldier’s eyes, and falling in love.

When danger lands at their doorstep, Natalia and Tony have to pack up and leave, running away in the middle of the night and leaving their men behind.

The distance between Tony and Bucky gets longer every day, and Natalia has been keeping a secret for that can’t be hidden much longer. With no place to call home and a thousand miles between them and the men they love, what are Tony and Natalia supposed to do?

*********************

summary: Oh, Snap
title: Oh, Snap
body:
read it on the AO3 at http://bit.ly/2DQ6c8s

by wedelia

Peter wakes up, and he’s simultaneously five years too early and right on time.

Or, Post-Endgame Peter goes back in time and accidentally-on-purpose gets Steve and Tony together before the initial snap happens. And, oh, yeah—he also recruits a former-Air-Force-pilot-turned-galactic-hero, has lunch with Black Widow, and somehow befriends Nick Fury. This changes things.
